## 🏁 Summary

v1.2 focuses on making the app feel **intelligent and responsive**, with:

* smarter input handling
* reduced friction
* improved discoverability of NLP features

These changes move the app closer to an **AI-assisted conversion experience**, rather than a traditional unit converter.


### 🔄 Hybrid Category Model (NLP + Manual)

The app uses a **hybrid category discovery model** combining traditional UI with NLP-driven expansion.

#### 🎯 Initial State

* App starts with a **curated set of 6–9 categories**
* Ensures immediate usability via manual mode

#### 🧠 Dynamic Expansion via NLP

* When a user enters a valid NLP query for a hidden category:

  * That category is **automatically surfaced in the UI**
  * No manual discovery required

#### 🔁 LRU-Based Category Management

* Maximum visible categories: **~15**
* When limit is reached:

  * Least Recently Used (LRU) category is evicted
* Ensures UI remains clean and relevant

#### ⭐ Integration with Favorites

* Selecting a favorite conversion:

  * Brings its category back into view
  * Triggers LRU eviction if needed

---

### 💡 Why This Approach

| Approach                | Trade-off                                |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Static categories only  | Easy but cluttered                       |
| NLP-only (0 categories) | Powerful but confusing                   |
| **Hybrid (chosen)**     | Best balance of usability + intelligence |

---

### 🚀 Benefits

* Immediate usability (manual mode)
* Discoverability via NLP
* Personalized UI over time
* Scales well as more categories are added

---

### 🧠 Design Insight

The UI acts as a **cache of user intent**, not a fixed structure.

* Frequently used categories stay visible
* Rare ones fade out automatically
* NLP acts as the **primary discovery mechanism**

---

### 🔮 Future Enhancements

* Smarter LRU (frequency + recency)
* Category pinning (user-controlled)
* Recently used category section
* Adaptive category ordering

